## Project Layout

```text
src/
├── main/
│   ├── java/{{ base_package | replace('.', '/') }}/
│   │   ├── config/
│   │   ├── web/
│   │   ├── web/dto/
│   │   ├── service/
│   │   ├── domain/
│   │   ├── repository/
│   │   └── security/
│   └── resources/
└── test/
    ├── java/{{ base_package | replace('.', '/') }}/
    └── resources/
```

{% if use_ddd %}
This blueprint assumes a DDD-leaning package split. Keep domain rules inside `domain/` and orchestrate use cases from `service/` or dedicated application services.
{% else %}
This blueprint assumes a conventional Spring layered architecture. Keep controllers thin, service classes cohesive, and repositories persistence-focused.
{% endif %}

## Getting Started

### 1. Clone and enter the project

```bash
git clone <repo-url> {{ project_name }}
cd {{ project_name }}
```

### 2. Configure local settings

Create an `application-local.yml` or set environment variables for local development.

```yaml
spring:
  application:
    name: {{ project_name }}
  datasource:
{% if database == "postgresql" %}
    url: jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/{{ project_name | replace('-', '_') }}
    driver-class-name: org.postgresql.Driver
{% elif database == "mysql" %}
    url: jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/{{ project_name | replace('-', '_') }}
    driver-class-name: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver
{% else %}
    url: jdbc:mariadb://localhost:3306/{{ project_name | replace('-', '_') }}
    driver-class-name: org.mariadb.jdbc.Driver
{% endif %}
    username: app
    password: change-me
{% if use_auth and auth_method == "jwt" %}
app:
  security:
    jwt-secret: change-me-to-a-long-random-value
{% elif use_auth and auth_method == "oauth2" %}
spring:
  security:
    oauth2:
      resourceserver:
        jwt:
          issuer-uri: https://issuer.example.com/realms/main
{% elif use_auth and auth_method == "api-key" %}
app:
  security:
    api-key-header: X-API-Key
{% endif %}
{% if use_redis %}
spring:
  data:
    redis:
      host: localhost
      port: 6379
{% endif %}
{% if use_kafka %}
spring:
  kafka:
    bootstrap-servers: localhost:9092
{% endif %}
```

### 3. Install dependencies and run the app

{% if build_tool == "maven" %}
```bash
./mvnw spring-boot:run
./mvnw test
```
{% else %}
```bash
./gradlew bootRun
./gradlew test
```
{% endif %}

The default local endpoint is typically `http://localhost:8080`.

## Testing

{% if test_strategy == "junit-only" %}
Use JUnit 5 for unit and slice tests. Prefer `@WebMvcTest`, `@DataJpaTest`, and plain service tests before adding full integration coverage.
{% elif test_strategy == "junit-and-testcontainers" %}
Use JUnit 5 plus Testcontainers for integration tests. Database-backed repository tests should run against a real container, not H2 in compatibility mode.
{% else %}
Use a full test pyramid: unit tests, Spring slice tests, Testcontainers-backed integration tests, and a small number of end-to-end API smoke tests.
{% endif %}

{% if build_tool == "maven" %}
```bash
./mvnw test
./mvnw verify
```
{% else %}
```bash
./gradlew test
./gradlew check
```
{% endif %}

## Code Quality

Recommended checks:

- Spotless or formatter plugin for code style
- Checkstyle or PMD for static rules
- Error Prone or NullAway if the team uses them
- ArchUnit for package-boundary rules
- Testcontainers for real integration paths

